children.subject: Wait, major decisions are out right now?
For the fifth year masters an advisor, or a professor in EECS to write one of your letters of recs to sponsor you - do you have that?

history.content:
Hello all,

I just recently declared the CS Major and am set to graduate this semester (added CS as a double major recently). I'm considering applying for a the 5th year MS program, however all my internships/great connections with professors are from my other degree, civil engineering. 

I'm curious as to whether or not I can submit letters of rec from faculty outside of CS/managers that aren't in software or whether I should attempt to reach out to some of my professors from last semester/this semester.
